Scotland Yard Flying Squad released images of three suspects in the Hatton Garden raid on Saturday . 
  Criminologist Richard Hoskins has identified 'striking similarities' between the raid and novel Black Echo . 
  The crime novel is based on two jewel heists in LA in the 1980s . 
  The Hole In The Ground Gang struck three vaults in 1986 and 1987 . 
  Police have identified one of the men in the raid but have not named him . 
  Officers refused to release images of the supposed ringleader . 
 